# A [[noun]] that normally cannot be [[count]]ed.
#:''In English, '''mass nouns''', such as ''information'' and ''money'', usually have no plural form and are almost never used with the indefinite article ''a'', ''an'', or ''numbers'' (ex: an information, a money, 7 information, 7 money).''

====Usage notes====
Some mass nouns, such as ''[[whisky]]'', can also be count nouns when they refer to a variety (“Scotch and Canadian whiskies”) or in informal usage to denote a serving (“please bring us two whiskies”).

